TI  - <ref>Sherman, John. [https://www.bkmag.com/2014/08/06/why-is-brooklyns-flag-so-lame/ "Why Is Brooklyn's Flag So Lame?"] date=January 19, 2024 , Brooklyn Magazine, August 6, 2014. Accessed January 18, 2024. "If you aren't familiar, Brooklyn has a flag. And it's a bummer. It's plain white, first of all, with a sort of wonky blue oval shape at the center. Inside the oval is a bored-looking woman in a yellow robe, carrying a fasces, a symbol of unity. The oval is ringed with a motto, in Dutch, Een Draght Maekt Maght ('Unity Makes Strength'), and the words Borough of Brooklyn."
